/a>”之前不会发布任何电动汽车。加拿大亿万富翁斯特罗尔也是阿斯顿·马丁 F1 车队的所有者，他早在 2020 年就持有阿斯顿·马丁 25% 的股份。与此同时，梅赛德斯-奔驰目前拥有阿斯顿·马丁 9.4% 的股份，此前曾表示计划将其增至 20%到 2023 年将达到 10%。</p><p>作为该交易的一部分，梅赛德斯-奔驰允许阿斯顿·马丁使用其混合动力和电动动力系统，但目前尚不清楚 Lucid 和梅赛德斯将如何互动。阿斯顿·马丁的 F1 车队目前使用梅赛德斯-奔驰动力装置，但计划在 2026 年改用本田。“与梅赛德斯-奔驰一起，我们现在拥有两家世界级供应商（Lucid）来支持我们的内部开发和投资。正在努力实现我们的电气化战略，”斯特罗尔说。</p><p> Rimac 为阿斯顿·马丁的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/aston-martin-valkyrie-heads-public-100000985.html">1,160 马力 Valkyrie 超级跑车</a><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.carthrottle.com/post/the-aston-martin-valkyrie-has-a-1160bhp-total-output-thanks-to-rimac/">提供了技术</a>，包括轻型电池系统。早在2015年，阿斯顿·马丁就与乐视联手打造了<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.autoblog.com/2019/04/15/aston-martin-rapide-e-electric-fd7ks49g/">Rapide的电动版</a>，但乐视却因自身财务问题<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-07-20-leeco-jia-yueting-investigation.html">而退出</a>。为了完成这个圈子，乐视原本持有Lucid的股份，但创始人贾跃亭因流动性危机<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.vox.com/2017/7/20/15999024/lucid-motors-ford-funding-tesla-electric-car">被迫出售</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/lucid-will-power-aston-martins-future-evs-101040684.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/lucid-will-power-aston-martins-future-evs-101040684.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5156493c-8db5-48dc-a93b-0642d028289f</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 26 Jun 2023 10:10:40 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687774245</ingested><modified> 2023-06-26T10:10:49+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1663" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/5e27ff70-13fc-11ee-871e-98db04019c8f" width="2511"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1663" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/5e27ff70-13fc-11ee-871e-98db04019c8f" width="2511"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lucid Group]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Lucid has entered into a definitive agreement to establish a long-term strategic technology partnership with Aston Martin to accelerate the iconic British brandâ€™s high-performance electrification strategy and long-term growth. The agreement will see Aston Martin gain access to Lucidâ€™s ultra-high performance twin motor drive unit, battery technology, and Wunderbox, as well as technical support from Lucid in integrating its proprietary technology.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Lucid-twin-motor-drive-unit]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Netflix is removing its 'basic' plan in Canada]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>加拿大用户再次成为 Netflix 新政策的非自愿首批采用者。据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/entertainment/movies/2023/06/23/netflix-phases-out-basic-streaming-plan-from-its-subscription-options-in-canada"><em>温尼伯自由报</em>报道，</a>继二月份决定对加拿大家庭之间的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflix-account-sharing-rollout-countries-202340036.html">帐户共享收取更多费用</a>后，该流媒体现在宣布其基本计划将不再成为加拿大订阅者的选择。</p><p>任何已经使用基本计划的人都不必担心被踢出该计划，但如果他们选择转向其他选项或关闭帐户，他们就无法回到该级别。新用户无法再选择基本选项，而其他计划的当前订阅者将失去“在不久的将来”切换的机会。在加拿大，基本套餐为每月 9.99 美元（加元），带广告的基本套餐为 5.99 美元，标准套餐为 16.49 美元，高级套餐为 20.99 美元。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在声称<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflix-ad-supported-plan-password-sharing-charge-2022-160931971.html">永远不会提供广告支持选项</a>后，Netflix 于 2022 年 11 月做到了这一点，在加拿大、美国和其他 10 个国家/地区推出了新的套餐。现在，随着决定取消其基本选项，该流媒体正在推动更多客户获得充满广告的观看体验。理由很简单：广告支持的计划对 Netflix 的利润非常有利。 2023 年第一季度，在美国各地， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://ir.netflix.net/investor-news-and-events/financial-releases/press-release-details/2023/Netflix-Releases-First-Quarter-2023-Financial-Results/default.aspx">Netflix 的基本广告套餐为每个用户带来的收入比其标准套餐更多</a>。尽管其广告等级为 6.99 美元，而标准计划的成本为 15.49 美元，但这种二分法仍然存在。</p><p>没有迹象表明 Netflix 会很快在美国取消基本套餐，但如果你想避免支付更多费用或观看广告，现在可能是选择它的时候了。在美国，基本计划为 9.99 美元，保费为 19.99 美元。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/netflix-is-removing-its-basic-plan-in-canada-092535002.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/netflix-is-removing-its-basic-plan-in-canada-092535002.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> bd05d848-1e16-4ecf-af16-11c544359ecd</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 26 Jun 2023 09:25:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687770941</ingested><modified> 2023-06-26T09:15:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-06/d621d540-f31f-11ec-9ff5-49b6bb80041e" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-06/d621d540-f31f-11ec-9ff5-49b6bb80041e" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Justin Sullivan via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[LOS GATOS, CALIFORNIA - APRIL 20: A sign is posted in front of Netflix headquarters on April 20, 2022 in Los Gatos, California. Shares of Netflix dropped over 35 percent after the company reported that it had lost 200,000 subscribers for the first time in the first quarter. The company also reported that it expects to lose an additional 2 million subscribers in the current quarter. (Photo by Justin Sullivan/Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Netflix Reports Drop In Quarterly Earnings]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[NASA is creating a ChatGPT-like assistant for astronauts]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>尽管<em>《2001：太空漫游》</em> （“ <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:YouTube;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=89f68c82-f255-44fa-8db9-03fec996b93a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=YouTube&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4OWY2OGM4Mi1mMjU1LTQ0ZmEtOGRiOS0wM2ZlYzk5NmI5M2EiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1NbWUyQXlhXzZCYyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNWNkOGEzYjAtZjNiMC00MmY3LTgyODYtOWFhNjdiYzA3MWI4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAeoCanRjndBJpyp60d3Apd8zUbt67OL1ugwEVmtZQ4Sq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DMme2Aya_6Bc" class="rapid-with-clickid">恐怕我做不到，戴夫</a>”）等电影告诉我们，我们对太空中的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/many-americans-distrust-emerging-technology-new-study-finds-170038843.html">人工智能本质上不信任</a>，但它为载人和无人任务提供了巨大的优势。据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/jun/24/nasa-spaceships-talk-chatgpt-larissa-suzuki"><em>《卫报》</em></a>报道，为此，NASA 正在开发一种系统，允许宇航员使用类似 ChatGPT 的自然语言界面进行机动、进行实验等。</p><p>拉里萨·铃木 (Larissa Suzuki) 博士在大会上发言时表示：“我们的想法是，我们与太空飞行器进行对话式互动，而它们也会向我们回复警报、他们在太阳系及其他地方看到的有趣发现。”关于下一代空间通信的 IEEE 会议。 “这真的不再像科幻小说了。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>美国宇航局的目标是在其<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spacex-lunar-gateway-launch-contract-231142514.html">月球门户空间站</a>上部署该系统，该空间站将绕月球运行并为美国宇航局的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.nasa.gov/content/humans-on-the-moon/index.html">阿耳忒弥斯任务</a>提供支持。它将使用自然语言界面，允许宇航员寻求有关实验的建议或进行演习，而无需深入研究复杂的手册。</p><p>美国宇航局在<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://sbir.nasa.gov/content/autonomous-systems-and-operations-lunar-orbital-platform-gateway-1">专门为月球门户征求小企业支持的页面</a>上写道，月球门户需要人工智能和机器学习技术来管理各种系统（当月球门户闲置时）。其中包括科学有效载荷的自主操作、数据传输优先级、自主操作、网关的健康管理等。</p><p>例如，铃木概述了一种场景，在该场景中，系统将自动修复数据传输故障和效率低下，以及其他类型的数字中断。她说：“每当航天器离线或软件出现故障时，我们就无法将工程师送上太空。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/nasa-is-creating-a-chatgpt-like-assistant-for-astronauts-081903604.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nasa-is-creating-a-chatgpt-like-assistant-for-astronauts-081903604.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5cd8a3b0-f3b0-42f7-8286-9aa67bc071b8</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 26 Jun 2023 08:19:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687767544</ingested><modified> 2023-06-26T08:19:08+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1080" mediu